text: Jeotgalicoccus nanhaiensis is a gram-positive bacterium.Zhu-Xiang Liu, Jun Chen, Shu-Kun Tang, Yu-Qin Zhang, Jian-Wu He, Qi-Hui Chen, Wen-Jun Li and Yi- Guang Chen: Jeotgalicoccus nanhaiensis sp. nov., isolated from intertidal sediment, and emended description of the genus Jeotgalicoccus In: International journal of systematic and evolutionary microbiology. 2011, 61, 2029-2034. The cells of Jeotgalicoccus nanhaiensis are coccoid. Spores are not formed. Jeotgalicoccus nanhaiensis belongs to the family Staphylococcaceae. ==References== Category:Gram-positive bacteria
title: Jeotgalicoccus nanhaiensis
